HEADWORD: Eurafrican
<hw>Eur*af"ri*can</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Europe</ets> +
<ets>Afric</ets>, <ets>African</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Geog.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, the
continents of Europe and Africa combined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧geography)</fld> <def>Pert. to or
designating a region including most of Europe and northern Africa south
to the Sahara.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of European and African descent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eurasian</ent>⟦br⟧
